---
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Breadcrumb from '../../../components/Breadcrumb.astro';
---

<Layout title="Coronary Artery Disease — Dr Delhasse, Cardiologist" description="Angina pectoris, heart attack: understanding coronary artery disease and its management by Dr Delhasse." lang="en">

  <section class="hero-page">
    <div class="container">
      <Breadcrumb items={[{label:'Home', href:'/en'}, {label:'Areas of Expertise', href:'/en/areas-of-expertise'}, {label:'Coronary Artery Disease'}]} />
      <h1>Coronary Artery <span class="text-primary">Disease</span></h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">Angina: the warning signal from your arteries</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container detail-content">
      <img src="/images/detail/maladie-coronarienne.webp" alt="Coronary artery disease" class="detail-hero-img" />
      <img src="/images/svg/expertise/Maladie-coronarienne.svg" alt="Coronary artery disease" class="detail-icon" />

      <p>Coronary artery disease manifests as angina pectoris (chest tightness on exertion) or a heart attack, resulting from narrowing of the coronary arteries by cholesterol plaques, which disrupts the heart's blood supply.</p>

      <p>It can cause chest pain, rhythm disorders, or in severe cases, a heart attack. Progressive narrowing can be slowed or prevented through preventive approaches. Identifying risk factors with your doctor allows appropriate protective measures to be taken.</p>

      <p>When patients present with persistent angina symptoms and the ECG is inconclusive, coronary angiography must be performed promptly. Angina, often indicating myocardial ischaemia, occurs when the heart's oxygen demands exceed the blood supply due to narrowing (atherosclerosis) or arterial spasm, typically during exertion.</p>

      <p>It is important to manage symptoms while taking prescribed anti-anginal medications. The cardiologist will check for other vascular complications through a comprehensive vascular assessment for optimal care.</p>

      <div class="detail-cta">
        <a href="/en/areas-of-expertise" class="btn btn--outline-dark">&larr; All areas</a>
        <a href="/en/contact" class="btn btn--primary">Book an appointment</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>

<style>
  .hero-page { background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--color-navy) 0%, #1a3d6d 100%); padding: 6rem 0 4rem; color: var(--color-white); }
  .hero-page h1 { color: var(--color-white); font-size: 2.75rem; }
  .hero-sub { color: rgba(255,255,255,0.75); font-size: 1.15rem; margin-top: 1rem; }
  .detail-content { max-width: 800px; }
  .detail-icon { width: 80px; height: 80px; margin-bottom: 2rem; }
  .detail-hero-img { width: 100%; height: 300px; object-fit: cover; border-radius: 8px; margin-bottom: 2rem; }
  .detail-content p { font-size: 1.05rem; line-height: 1.8; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; color: var(--color-gray); }
  .detail-cta { display: flex; gap: 1rem; margin-top: 3rem; flex-wrap: wrap; }
  @media (max-width: 768px) { .hero-page h1 { font-size: 2rem; } }
</style>
